    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_80f0dfc9",
      "file_path": "vid-app-common/src/main/java/org/onap/vid/controller/PropertyController.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 52,
      "message": "I agree with unified solution, but...\n\nWhile introducing another class for such stupid thing seems bad it has some pros:\n\n\n1) meaningful class and method names\n\nCompare both ways:\n\n properties.getProperty(\"foo\")\n\n propertyGetter.apply(\"foo\")\n\n\nPersonally I found first one more appealing.\n\n\n2) we can extend wrapper with method like:\n\n properties.getOrDefault(\"foo\", \"kuku shmuku\")\n\n\nRight now both PropertyController and SchedulerRestInterface (one can expect more to come) reinventing this \"orDefault\" construction.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2731,
        "name": "KK",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "krzysztof.kurczewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "kurczews"
      },
      "updated": "2019-01-22 06:14:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9adffdf1_8061bfd4",
      "unresolved": false
    },
